https://justjoin.it//offers/sigma-it-pol.description:
Sigma IT Poland is a division within NEXER GROUP – a custom software development company. In Poland, we started in 2017 and now we are 180+ crew with an office in Wrocław, Warsaw, and Cracow. We have the opportunity to work with world-renowned brands from Scandinavia, the UK, and Western Europe. Our goal is to grow stronger, rather in competencies than in pure numbers. If you like what we do, see our offer, maybe it is you we will have the pleasure to meet! 🚀Are you driven by a passion for automotive software testing and development? If you excel in Python programming, possess a solid background in test automation, and are adept at working with GIT and Jenkins, we have an exciting opportunity for you – join us as a DevOps Engineer! As a vital member of our team, you will play a pivotal role in developing and maintaining tools for test automation and framework, focusing on visualizing test results. Your excellent communication, multitasking, problem-solving, and planning skills will be key assets in contributing to our dynamic work environment. You might be the perfect match if you are/have:
At least 5 years of automotive test or development experience;
Proficiency in Python programming;
Adept at working with GIT and Jenkins;
Robot framework (or similar keyword-based test framework). 
GIT and Jenkins knowledge;
Familiarity with data visualization tools;
Test automation knowledge;
CAN, LIN, and Ethernet knowledge. 
Moreover, we appreciate skills in these areas:
MatLab;
Simulink; 
dSPACE HW and SW.
By joining us, you gain the following:

Exciting projects, a multinational and inspiring environment for talented IT professionals. Various projects in diverse, cutting-edge industries. Biotech, Automotive, Internet of Things, or AR/VR;
Code review done by skilled engineers (over 60% of our team are people with over 5 years of experience in the industry);
Becoming a part of a team of motivated individuals, that are here to stay. We value loyalty – as you grow, we grow with you;

Respect for your private life so you don't have to work overtime or on weekends;

Online and offline integration events - including remote X-mass party and annual WOW tour trip abroad - so far we've been in Cape Town and Barcelona.
Perks and benefits:

Fully remote work from your convenience or in our office in Wrocław, Warsaw or Cracow;
Choice of employment form: we offer B2B or employment contract;
Free benefits such as Luxmed, Multisport, and life insurance in Nationale Nederlanden;
Attractive referral system (9,1k for senior, 5,7k for mid, 2,3k for junior);

Personal Training Budget and Passion Day - an extra day off for your passion, hobby, and growth to spend as you please;

Flexible working hours with no micro-management approach. Our core hours are 9-15, the rest of the working time is your decision;
We provide high-quality work equipment + 2 additional monitors and accessories.
If you apply for this position and match our expectations, then:1) You will be invited to talk with Agnieszka and our Technical Recruiter. 2) You will have a final meeting with our client.Submit your application online in one easy step! Apply now!

